## 2ï¸âƒ£ Generate SSH Key (Recommended)

Check if you already have one:

```bash
ls ~/.ssh
```

If not:

```bash
ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "you@example.com"
```

Press **Enter** for defaults.

Start SSH agent:

```bash
eval "$(ssh-agent -s)"
ssh-add ~/.ssh/id_ed25519
```

Copy public key:

```bash
cat ~/.ssh/id_ed25519.pub
```

ğŸ‘‰ GitHub â†’ **Settings â†’ SSH and GPG keys â†’ New SSH key**
Paste it â†’ Save.

Test connection:

```bash
ssh -T git@github.com
```

You should see:

> Hi username! You've successfully authenticated...

---

## 3ï¸âƒ£ Connect Local Repo to GitHub

Inside your project folder:

```bash
cd git-demo
```

Add GitHub as remote:

```bash
git remote add origin git@github.com:USERNAME/git-demo.git
```

Verify:

```bash
git remote -v
```

---

## 4ï¸âƒ£ Push Code to GitHub

If branch is `master`, rename to `main` (GitHub standard):

```bash
git branch -M main
```

Push:

```bash
git push -u origin main
```

ğŸ‰ Refresh GitHub â†’ your files are there.

