## 5ï¸âƒ£ Clone a Repo (New Machine / Folder)

```bash
cd ~
git clone git@github.com:USERNAME/git-demo.git
cd git-demo
```

---

## 6ï¸âƒ£ Typical Daily Workflow

### Make changes

```bash
nano hello.txt
```

### Check status

```bash
git status
```

### Stage & commit

```bash
git add .
git commit -m "Update message"
```

### Push to GitHub

```bash
git push
```

---

## 7ï¸âƒ£ Pull Changes from GitHub

If someone else (or another machine) updated the repo:

```bash
git pull
```

---

## 8ï¸âƒ£ Branch + Push to GitHub

```bash
git checkout -b feature-login
echo "Login feature" > login.txt
git add .
git commit -m "Add login feature"
git push -u origin feature-login
```

Now GitHub will show:

> **Compare & Pull Request**

